  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2025",
  "title": "Ease multi index and autocomplete with react-instantsearch",
  "body": "This a preview of what I've done to ease the multi index / autocomplete use case by using react-instantsearch. \r\n\r\nI'd love to have your feedback of what is already done. You can play with the feature by looking at the story \"Multi Index\". I also updated two recipes for you to see the changes. \r\n\r\nWhile developing this feature I change some internal implementations: \r\n* The query is now added as a metadata. The `connectCurrentRefinement` filter them if the prop `clearsQuery` is not their. \r\n* The pagination reset to first page is now explicitly done by each widget that needs it\r\n* When unmounting a widget, we clear the empty key from the `search state`. Will probably be moved to the `onSearchStateChange` function. \r\n\r\nWhat I want to do next with this branch: \r\n\r\n* refactor the derivation usage inside `createInstantSearchManager`. I added some basic tests to support this refactoring. @bobylito if you have any advice, pleases shoot :) \r\n* add a real autocomplete example without the usage of an external component. Don't know if we should go for a recipe, or do a nice demo. \r\n* update all the documentation => api, guide. \r\n \r\nsee #1962",
